			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">What to do in groups?<a name="28943"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 19 04 2:31 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Am I just too self-assured in my abilities as a Bard or are people just too thickheaded to see what a Bard can do?
<br />

<br />
Lately in LDoN groups I feel as if I am reduced to nothing in others eyes. 
<br />

<br />
In a normal group I try and become the puller of the group (if there is no monk around). I know that I can pull fast and have single mobs 98% of the time. 
<br />

<br />
I say 98% of the time because there are some instances where you get a lull resist and three mobs come charging at you. In which case I can instantly whip out mez until the enchanter has things under control. 
<br />

<br />
Anyway, the general pull set up is to play Kellin's Lucid Lullaby (with or without a lute, depends on who's in the group) then agro a mob with Selo's Consonant Chain. 
<br />

<br />
This gives me time to get back to the group and start twisting. As well as gives the tank time to fire an arrow at the mob or cast a spell to grab agro. 
<br />

<br />
My typical group song line up is: 1) Amplification 2) Villia's Verses of Celerity 3) Hymn of Restoration 4) Casindra's Chorus of Clarity (SoE really needs to just change the name of this to &quot;mana song&quot;, since people still whine I don't play it). 
<br />

<br />
I'm still unsure if Cantata of Soothing is better than Hymn + Casindra's. It seems that Hymn just gives back more hp. 
<br />

<br />
I'll occasionally switch out Amplification with Jaxan's Jig o' Vigor if there is a Berserker in the group.
<br />

<br />
I can twist 4 songs considering I don't miss a note or have lag.  
<br />

<br />
I'll melee (despite my low weapon skill) or have my lute in hand depending on the situation. 
<br />
-----
<br />
Is that what is expected of a Bard in a typical group situation?
<br />

<br />
Lately when in a group I've been receiving tells from Enchanters and Paladins saying &quot;What are you doing? Bards don't pull, sit back and play mana songs please.&quot;
<br />

<br />
In one case I've even had an Enchanter tell me &quot;I'm the puller and mezer! I only invited you to sit back and play mana song. Stop interfering with me.&quot;
<br />

<br />
I've even had tanks (Warriors, Berserkers etc.) run around pulling trains. Insisting that lull pulling is too slow. 
<br />

<br />
I have also been called a &quot;Taxi&quot;. Last night the Enchanter in the group insisted that I ran to the gfay zone line in lfay and run him back to our group at the Mistmore LDoN zone in place. I thought he was joking at first, however he wasn't. 
<br />

<br />
So what did I do? I sat back and played my usual line up of songs. I'm not one to tell classes what to do or how to play. I know it pisses people off. So I just do as I'm told.  
<br />
-----
<br />
Now for my question. What is a Bard's role in a group?
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
