				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What to do in groups?<a name="28946"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 19 04 2:42 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I would have likely told people like that to re-roll a Bard PL it up, and 2 Box it if they just need a Mana Battery.
<br />

<br />
Bards Pull better in LDoN than ANY OTHER CLASS, Period.  These people were just likely used to playing with one hit wonder Bards that were PLed and have no idea how to play their class.
<br />

<br />
Bard bring so much more to a group than what they were asking.  You could likely cut mission time by at least 1/4.  When I play my Druid in an LDoN group we usually take a little over an hour or so per LDoN without a Bard.  When I play my Bard in the same group of folks we can finish anywhere from 30 minutes to an hour depending on drop rate room makeup etc.
<br />

<br />
I might finish the adventure if we are already in, but it would be clear before the adventure ends for them not to ask me to do another.  I'll go find a competent group who will allow me to use my talents to make the group overall more efficient. 
<br />

<br />
With the Enchanter in the group there should have been little to no problems with people needing mana song.  And then it would likely only be because A.  The tank keeps pulling trains, or B.  You had a lull resist, and brought in 4 or 5 mobs, and the cleric had to do alot of healing.
<br />

<br />
Sounds like the Enchanter just wanted to pull is all, they were just going about it with the wrong attitude.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
