				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What to do in groups?<a name="28950"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 19 04 3:10 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Bards are the best pullers in LDoN and in any situation where lull or Fading memories will work.  
<br />

<br />
When FD is needed Necromancers are great pullers, they get <b>three chances to FD</b> and have Harmshield and mez and AAs like instant invis to undead and the pre-nerf CoS to boot,  followed by SKs two chances to FD and pre-nerf CoS, followed by monks as FD pullers.  
<br />

<br />
Monk lull is over rated, it's single use and can only reduce a pull by one mob.  
<br />

<br />
Being able to lull mutliple mobs even with a chance for a resist on the first, second (reduced the pull by one already), or third lull (pull reduced by two already) is really unimportant, as it's still better than being forced to pull X - 1, when it could be X - 2 with a resist or even X - 3 with a resist.  
<br />

<br />
Plus we have Fading memories and a plethera of other pulling tools,  I've enjoyed reading about.
<br />

<br />
We are the best pullers in the game.
<br />
Pull and be happy.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
