			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What to do in groups?<a name="28953"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 19 04 3:20 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Excellent way to put it.  We have more -- and in many cases better -- tools at our disposal than monks.
<br />

<br />
That doesn't make us automatically the best pullers.  Like everything, it's situational.
<br />

<br />
Monks have been the main pullers for the last 4 years or so.  Many of them have a LOT of experience pulling and a LOT of skill at doing it well.  Many bards, even with the excellent tools we have, are still learning how.
<br />

<br />
Also, the monk's one main tool -- feign death -- is still superior to fade in some situations.  Most notably where mobs see inviso and there's not a lot of room to play with placement.
<br />

<br />
So, for some pulls the monk will be suprior to the bard.  For others, the bard will be superior to the monk.  The bard can usually do it faster than the monk, which makes a big difference in many situations.  And all these claims assume players of equal skill, which is a big and often invalid assumption.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
