				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What to do in groups?<a name="28954"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 19 04 3:29 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I'll echo the sentiments of the previous posters.
<br />

<br />
Our role is to fill in and make the group better.  Often that means pulling, buffs (eg. mana), haste/slow, snare, mez.
<br />

<br />
The enchanter demanding you be taxi service was just plain rude.  I don't mind driving the selos bus for the group but I'm not likely to go back and pick someone up (I have the long duration selos so one pulse is enough to get across the majority of zones).
<br />

<br />
Saying lull pulling is too slow as a general statement is silly.  However, there are people that religiously lull every mob and then pull.  Lull is a pulling tool.  Some people use it well; others use it very poorly.
<br />

<br />
You say you pull singles almost all the time, and that is not a bad thing.  However, I would suggest you try mixing it up a bit and experiment with purposely pulling doubles.  The key is not that only one mob arrives in camp at a time -- it's that mobs don't arrive all at the same time.  Hitting one with mez on the way in and having it arrive 3-4 ticks later means you don't have to leave the group to grab another.  Pullling singles or multiples is a bit of a judgement call based on the group's capabilities.  Sometimes it's more efficient, sometimes it's not.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
