				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: question<a name="29465"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 22 04 4:08 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>That's just mobs with huge primary, assist and chase radiuses.  I dont know of course no one does.
<br />

<br />
Fear, Hate and many other high end zones are exceptional and aggro just doesnt work as youd expect there.  One time you expect aggro and not get it another time you think youre safe that the whole d*mn zone aggro s you.  But generally speaking, aggro does work as circles around mobs, primary (the smallest circle), assist (the medium circle) and chase (a huge circle) around each mob.  The art of pulling is knowing the size of those circles before you lull, throw a fishbone dart or train your group.  The other part of being a puller is accepting the fact that you are going to die.  If you cant handle getting killed do not offer to pull.  Good pullers die rather than train their group with too many mobs. Wink, wink, nudge, nudge 
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
